<div class="container">
  <h1>About This Project</h1>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-8">
      <h2>Data Sources</h2>
      <p>This Ruby on Rails application pulls data from multiple sources to create a comprehensive Rick and Morty database:</p>

      <h3>1. Rick and Morty API</h3>
      <p>The primary data source is the <a href="https://rickandmortyapi.com/" target="_blank">Rick and Morty API</a>, which provides:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Characters:</strong> Information about all characters including their name, status, species, gender, origin, and current location</li>
        <li><strong>Locations:</strong> Details about dimensions, planets, and other locations in the Rick and Morty universe</li>
        <li><strong>Episodes:</strong> Complete episode information including air dates, episode codes, and character appearances</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>2. Faker Gem</h3>
      <p>Additional variety is provided through the Faker gem, which generates:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Additional fictional locations with random planet names and dimensions</li>
        <li>Extra characters with randomized attributes to demonstrate data handling</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Database Structure</h2>
      <p>The database is designed with the following relationships:</p>

      <h3>Models and Associations</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Character:</strong> Central model with references to origin and current locations</li>
        <li><strong>Location:</strong> Has many characters as residents and as origin</li>
        <li><strong>Episode:</strong> Connected to characters through a join table</li>
        <li><strong>CharacterEpisode:</strong> Join table managing many-to-many relationship between characters and episodes</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Key Features</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Search functionality across characters, locations, and episodes</li>
        <li>Filtering by status, species, and location type</li>
        <li>Hierarchical navigation between related models</li>
        <li>Responsive Bootstrap-based design</li>
        <li>Comprehensive character profiles with episode appearances</li>
        <li>Location pages showing residents and origin characters</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Technical Implementation</h2>
      <p>This application demonstrates:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>API integration and data parsing</li>
        <li>Complex database relationships (one-to-many and many-to-many)</li>
        <li>RESTful routing and MVC architecture</li>
        <li>Search and filtering functionality</li>
        <li>Responsive web design with Bootstrap</li>
        <li>Data validation and error handling</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-4">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-header">
          <h5>Database Statistics</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <ul class="list-unstyled">
            <li><strong>Characters:</strong> <%= Character.count %></li>
            <li><strong>Locations:</strong> <%= Location.count %></li>
            <li><strong>Episodes:</strong> <%= Episode.count %></li>
            <li><strong>Character-Episode Relations:</strong> <%= CharacterEpisode.count %></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card mt-3">
        <div class="card-header">
          <h5>Data Sources</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <ul class="list-unstyled">
            <li>✅ Rick and Morty API</li>
            <li>✅ Faker Gem</li>
            <li>✅ 200+ Database Records</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

